<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057112-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 6 and A = 10 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
c = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>34.0</li><li>34.6</li><li>80.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({10}\right)}}}=\frac{{6}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{6}}{{\tan{{\left({10}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{34.027690917706}\approx{34}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={6}^{{2}}+{34.027690917706}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={36}+{1157.8837491909}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={1193.8837491909}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{1193.8837491909}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{34.552622898862}\approx{34.6}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{10}^{\circ}\approx{80}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>